{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_eRfDxZ6MsdV5PPaNl8oPfnyj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI have created a comprehensive implementation plan at `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md` for ticket TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement.\n\n### Key Adaptations from Research Findings\n\n| PRD Assumption | Research Finding | Plan Adaptation |\n|----------------|------------------|-----------------|\n| JWT claims auth | X-Profile-Key header auth | Custom `RbacWebFilter` parsing `X-Profile-Key` and `X-Profile-Auth` headers |\n| Redux state | Zustand with persistence | Extend existing Zustand store with SSE subscription |\n| WebSocket push | SSE already exists for flows | Extend SSE infrastructure for role notifications (lower complexity) |\n| Spring Security | Not in classpath | Custom WebFlux filters without Spring Security dependency |\n\n### Implementation Phases\n\n1. **Phase 1 (Days 1-3):** Backend foundation - RBAC filter, audit log table, caching with Caffeine\n2. **Phase 2 (Days 4-5):** Profile service integration - client, configuration, role resolution\n3. **Phase 3 (Days 6-8):** Frontend role sync - `useRoleGuard` hook, `RoleGuard` component, SSE subscription\n4. **Phase 4 (Days 9-10):** SSE role events endpoint - `RoleEventService`, `RoleEventsController`\n5. **Phase 5 (Days 11-12):** Testing - unit, integration, and performance tests\n\n### Key Technical Decisions\n\n- **No Spring Security**: Avoids dependency conflicts with existing WebFlux setup\n- **Caffeine caching**: Already in classpath, 5-minute TTL for role cache\n- **SSE over WebSocket**: Existing infrastructure, sufficient for unidirectional push\n- **Fail-closed**: Deny access if profile service unavailable\n- **Async audit logging**: Never block request path\n\n### Files Summary\n\n- **19 new backend files** (domain, filter, service, persistence, config, controller)\n- **3 new frontend files** (hook, component, tests)\n- **4 modified files** (profileStore.ts, AdminRoles.tsx, App.tsx, build.gradle)\n- **1 database migration** (rbac_audit_log table)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: add8a001ba5e1fa60 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 47734\ntool_uses: 24\nduration_ms: 355774</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e8271fef-d7fa-47ae-9a86-a79be1e8c480","uuid":"1dd0e48f-1af6-44eb-ac82-027536d98a22","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are a planner agent for ticket TST-001. Your task is to create a detailed implementation plan based on the PRD and research findings.\n\n## Ticket\nTST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\n## PRD Summary\n- Implement live RBAC enforcement for all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n- Add audit logging for role operations and 403 responses  \n- Frontend role guards must sync with session updates without page refresh\n- Tech stack: React + Zustand (frontend), Spring WebFlux (backend)\n\n## Key Research Findings\n1. **Auth Model**: Current system uses X-Profile-Key and X-Profile-Auth headers, NOT JWT\n2. **Frontend State**: Uses Zustand (not Redux) with persistence\n3. **Real-time**: SSE already exists for flows; PRD wants WebSocket but SSE could be extended\n4. **No existing security**: No Spring Security, no JWT libraries, no @PreAuthorize\n5. **Role storage**: Roles stored in profile document as `roles: string[]`\n\n## Key Files to Reference\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` - Zustand store with role checks\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileTypes.ts` - Profile type with roles array\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts` - API client with SSE subscription\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` - Admin role guard example\n\n## Required Integration Points\n1. Backend RBAC Filter: Spring WebFlux filter for POST/PUT/DELETE endpoints using X-Profile-Key header\n2. Audit Log Table: New Liquibase migration for audit_log table\n3. Frontend Role Sync: Extend SSE or add WebSocket for role change notifications\n4. Profile Service Integration: Backend validates roles against profile service\n\n## Output\nCreate a detailed implementation plan at `aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md` with:\n1. Milestones/iterations (backend first, then frontend sync)\n2. Specific files to create/modify\n3. Technical approach for each component\n4. Testing strategy\n\nFocus on practical implementation steps that account for the research findings (header-based auth, Zustand, SSE vs WebSocket decision).","agentId":"add8a001ba5e1fa60","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI have created a comprehensive implementation plan at `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md` for ticket TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement.\n\n### Key Adaptations from Research Findings\n\n| PRD Assumption | Research Finding | Plan Adaptation |\n|----------------|------------------|-----------------|\n| JWT claims auth | X-Profile-Key header auth | Custom `RbacWebFilter` parsing `X-Profile-Key` and `X-Profile-Auth` headers |\n| Redux state | Zustand with persistence | Extend existing Zustand store with SSE subscription |\n| WebSocket push | SSE already exists for flows | Extend SSE infrastructure for role notifications (lower complexity) |\n| Spring Security | Not in classpath | Custom WebFlux filters without Spring Security dependency |\n\n### Implementation Phases\n\n1. **Phase 1 (Days 1-3):** Backend foundation - RBAC filter, audit log table, caching with Caffeine\n2. **Phase 2 (Days 4-5):** Profile service integration - client, configuration, role resolution\n3. **Phase 3 (Days 6-8):** Frontend role sync - `useRoleGuard` hook, `RoleGuard` component, SSE subscription\n4. **Phase 4 (Days 9-10):** SSE role events endpoint - `RoleEventService`, `RoleEventsController`\n5. **Phase 5 (Days 11-12):** Testing - unit, integration, and performance tests\n\n### Key Technical Decisions\n\n- **No Spring Security**: Avoids dependency conflicts with existing WebFlux setup\n- **Caffeine caching**: Already in classpath, 5-minute TTL for role cache\n- **SSE over WebSocket**: Existing infrastructure, sufficient for unidirectional push\n- **Fail-closed**: Deny access if profile service unavailable\n- **Async audit logging**: Never block request path\n\n### Files Summary\n\n- **19 new backend files** (domain, filter, service, persistence, config, controller)\n- **3 new frontend files** (hook, component, tests)\n- **4 modified files** (profileStore.ts, AdminRoles.tsx, App.tsx, build.gradle)\n- **1 database migration** (rbac_audit_log table)"}],"totalDurationMs":355774,"totalTokens":47734,"totalToolUseCount":24,"usage":{"input_tokens":9101,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":38144,"output_tokens":489,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
