{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_yGhhInblXvthrET1xW5Tslff","type":"tool_result","content":"   575→### Phase 4: SSE Role Events Endpoint (Days 9-10)\n   576→**Goal:** Backend SSE endpoint for role change notifications\n   577→\n   578→#### 4.1 Role Event Service\n   579→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java`\n   580→\n   581→```java\n   582→@Service\n   583→public class RoleEventService {\n   584→\n   585→    private final Map<ProfileIdentity, Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent>> subscribers = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();\n   586→\n   587→    public Flux<RoleChangeEvent> subscribe(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   588→        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = Sinks.many().multicast().onBackpressureBuffer();\n   589→        subscribers.put(identity, sink);\n   590→\n   591→        return sink.asFlux()\n   592→            .doOnCancel(() -> subscribers.remove(identity))\n   593→            .doOnTerminate(() -> subscribers.remove(identity));\n   594→    }\n   595→\n   596→    public void notifyRoleChange(ProfileIdentity identity, List<String> roles) {\n   597→        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = subscribers.get(identity);\n   598→        if (sink != null) {\n   599→            sink.tryEmitNext(new RoleChangeEvent(roles, Instant.now()));\n   600→        }\n   601→    }\n   602→\n   603→    public void broadcastRoleChange(ProfileIdentity target, List<String> roles) {\n   604→        notifyRoleChange(target, roles);\n   605→    }\n   606→\n   607→    public record RoleChangeEvent(List<String> roles, Instant timestamp) {}\n   608→}\n   609→```\n   610→\n   611→#### 4.2 SSE Controller\n   612→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java`\n   613→\n   614→```java\n   615→@RestController\n   616→@RequestMapping(\"/api/profiles\")\n   617→public class RoleEventsController {\n   618→\n   619→    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n   620→\n   621→    @GetMapping(value = \"/role-events\", produces = MediaType.TEXT_EVENT_STREAM_VALUE)\n   622→    public Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> roleEvents(\n   623→            @RequestParam String namespace,\n   624→            @RequestParam String reference,\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"tool_qWaqYNlqBZaQ20pUy0Eo4Z7p","session_id":"e8271fef-d7fa-47ae-9a86-a79be1e8c480","uuid":"57cb5d53-2cdf-4eea-9888-efcde79bc3cd"}
