{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_qWaqYNlqBZaQ20pUy0Eo4Z7p","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The validation report has been created successfully. Let me provide a summary of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## Validation Complete\n\n**Status:** WARN\n\nI have completed the validation of the implementation plan for ticket TST-001. The validation report has been written to `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001-validation.md`.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Category | Verdict |\n|----------|---------|\n| **Overall** | **WARN** |\n| **Executability** | PASS |\n| **Dependencies** | PASS |\n| **Research Alignment** | PASS |\n| **Risk Assessment** | WARN |\n\n### Key Findings\n\n**Positive (PASS):**\n1. **Technology adaptations are correct** - The plan correctly adapts from JWT/Redux/WebSocket (PRD assumptions) to X-Profile-Key headers/Zustand/SSE (actual codebase)\n2. **All dependencies available** - Caffeine cache, WebFlux, PostgreSQL, Liquibase are all present in `build.gradle`\n3. **Database patterns aligned** - Migration follows existing conventions from `note_entry` table\n4. **Frontend integration verified** - Zustand store, role arrays, SSE infrastructure all confirmed\n\n**Issues (WARN):**\n1. **Component scan configuration** - The application uses profile-based component scanning (`@Profile(\"notes\")`, `@Profile(\"flowops\")`, etc.). The RBAC module needs to be added to ALL profiles or a shared configuration created.\n2. **Profile service integration** - The plan assumes `profileClient.fetchRoles()` exists, but no backend API for fetching profile roles by namespace/reference was found in the research.\n3. **RbacPathMatcher implementation** - Referenced but not fully specified in the plan.\n\n### Risk Register (8 items identified)\n\n| Risk ID | Description | Probability | Impact |\n|---------|-------------|-------------|--------|\n| R-001 | Profile service unavailable | Medium | High |\n| R-002 | Cache stale roles | Medium | Medium |\n| R-007 | Component scan misses RBAC beans | Medium | High |\n| R-008 | Missing profile service integration | High | High |\n\n### Recommendations\n\n1. **Add shared RBAC configuration** that works across all Spring profiles\n2. **Define profile service contract** or implement local role storage\n3. **Complete RbacPathMatcher implementation** with explicit path rules\n4. **Add feature flags** for gradual rollout (audit-only mode first)\n\n### Blockers\n\n**None identified.** The plan can proceed after addressing the WARN-level issues."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: acb3f449c5c83d7d3 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54262\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 178941</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e8271fef-d7fa-47ae-9a86-a79be1e8c480","uuid":"360cca45-ba5c-4a9e-85fc-40629858bae8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are a validator agent for ticket TST-001. Your task is to validate the implementation plan at `aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md` for executability and risk assessment.\n\n## Validation Checklist\n1. **Executability**: Can each task be implemented with the current codebase?\n2. **Dependencies**: Are all dependencies available (Caffeine, WebFlux, etc.)?\n3. **Research alignment**: Does the plan correctly address the research findings?\n4. **Risk assessment**: What are the main risks and how are they mitigated?\n\n## Key Context from Research\n- No Spring Security in classpath - plan correctly uses custom WebFlux filters\n- Zustand (not Redux) for state management\n- SSE already exists - plan extends it (good decision vs WebSocket)\n- X-Profile-Key header auth (not JWT)\n\n## Output\nWrite your validation report to `aidd/docs/plan/TST-001-validation.md` with:\n1. Validation summary (PASS/WARN/FAIL)\n2. Findings - any issues or concerns\n3. Recommendations - specific improvements if needed\n4. Risk register - high/medium/low risks with mitigation\n\nBe thorough but practical. Flag any blockers that would prevent implementation.","agentId":"acb3f449c5c83d7d3","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The validation report has been created successfully. Let me provide a summary of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## Validation Complete\n\n**Status:** WARN\n\nI have completed the validation of the implementation plan for ticket TST-001. The validation report has been written to `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001-validation.md`.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Category | Verdict |\n|----------|---------|\n| **Overall** | **WARN** |\n| **Executability** | PASS |\n| **Dependencies** | PASS |\n| **Research Alignment** | PASS |\n| **Risk Assessment** | WARN |\n\n### Key Findings\n\n**Positive (PASS):**\n1. **Technology adaptations are correct** - The plan correctly adapts from JWT/Redux/WebSocket (PRD assumptions) to X-Profile-Key headers/Zustand/SSE (actual codebase)\n2. **All dependencies available** - Caffeine cache, WebFlux, PostgreSQL, Liquibase are all present in `build.gradle`\n3. **Database patterns aligned** - Migration follows existing conventions from `note_entry` table\n4. **Frontend integration verified** - Zustand store, role arrays, SSE infrastructure all confirmed\n\n**Issues (WARN):**\n1. **Component scan configuration** - The application uses profile-based component scanning (`@Profile(\"notes\")`, `@Profile(\"flowops\")`, etc.). The RBAC module needs to be added to ALL profiles or a shared configuration created.\n2. **Profile service integration** - The plan assumes `profileClient.fetchRoles()` exists, but no backend API for fetching profile roles by namespace/reference was found in the research.\n3. **RbacPathMatcher implementation** - Referenced but not fully specified in the plan.\n\n### Risk Register (8 items identified)\n\n| Risk ID | Description | Probability | Impact |\n|---------|-------------|-------------|--------|\n| R-001 | Profile service unavailable | Medium | High |\n| R-002 | Cache stale roles | Medium | Medium |\n| R-007 | Component scan misses RBAC beans | Medium | High |\n| R-008 | Missing profile service integration | High | High |\n\n### Recommendations\n\n1. **Add shared RBAC configuration** that works across all Spring profiles\n2. **Define profile service contract** or implement local role storage\n3. **Complete RbacPathMatcher implementation** with explicit path rules\n4. **Add feature flags** for gradual rollout (audit-only mode first)\n\n### Blockers\n\n**None identified.** The plan can proceed after addressing the WARN-level issues."}],"totalDurationMs":178941,"totalTokens":54262,"totalToolUseCount":23,"usage":{"input_tokens":4062,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":49664,"output_tokens":536,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
