{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_28P90Rt8AN3Bt9re6fSA4HUN","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e8271fef-d7fa-47ae-9a86-a79be1e8c480","uuid":"c437a5e0-971c-4118-b2bd-32d5747f0c98","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md","oldString":"## AIDD:RISKS\n\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| RBAC filter performance | High | Caffeine cache with 5min TTL; async audit logging |\n| Cache stale roles | Medium | Cache invalidation on role change via SSE broadcast |\n| SSE connection drops | Low | Auto-reconnect with exponential backoff in frontend |\n| Missing audit logs | Medium | Async logging with error queue; never block request |\n| Profile service unavailable | High | Circuit breaker pattern; fail-closed (deny access) |","newString":"## AIDD:RISKS\n\n| Risk ID | Description | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---------|-------------|-------------|--------|------------|\n| R-001 | Profile service unavailable | Medium | High | Circuit breaker; fail-closed; cache roles |\n| R-002 | Cache stale roles after assignment | Medium | Medium | Cache invalidation on role change; TTL 5min |\n| R-003 | SSE connection memory leak | Low | Medium | Proper cleanup on disconnect; subscriber limits |\n| R-004 | Audit log write failures | Low | Medium | Async logging; error queue; never block request |\n| R-005 | RBAC filter performance degradation | Low | High | Caffeine cache; async audit; P95 target 10ms |\n| R-006 | Breaking change to existing APIs | Low | High | Feature flags; audit-only mode first; rollback |\n| R-007 | Component scan misses RBAC beans | Medium | High | Add to all profile configs; verify on startup |\n| R-008 | Missing profile service integration | High | High | Define contract; implement fallback to local DB |\n\n### Validation-Derived Risks (from TST-001-validation.md)\n\n**R-007: Component Scan Configuration**\nThe application uses profile-based component scanning. The RBAC module needs to be added to ALL profiles or a shared configuration created.\n- **Mitigation**: Create `RbacConfig.java` with `@Profile(\"!test\")` active in all non-test profiles\n\n**R-008: Profile Service Integration**\nThe plan assumes `profileClient.fetchRoles()` exists, but no backend API for fetching profile roles was found in research.\n- **Mitigation**: Define profile service contract or implement local role storage via `rbac_profile_roles` table","originalFile":"# Implementation Plan — TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\n**Status:** READY\n**Ticket:** TST-001\n**Updated:** 2026-03-18\n**Research Status:** warn (see research findings for PRD overrides)\n\n---\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nThis plan implements live RBAC enforcement for all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and frontend role synchronization. Based on research findings, we adapt the PRD assumptions to the actual codebase:\n\n| PRD Assumption | Research Finding | Adaptation |\n|----------------|------------------|------------|\n| JWT claims auth | X-Profile-Key header auth | Custom WebFlux filter with header parsing |\n| Redux state | Zustand with persistence | Extend Zustand store with SSE listener |\n| WebSocket push | SSE already exists for flows | Extend SSE for role notifications |\n| Spring Security | Not in classpath | Custom WebFlux filters (no Spring Security) |\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:DECISIONS\n\n### Architecture Decisions\n\n1. **No Spring Security** — Adding spring-boot-starter-security introduces significant complexity and potential conflicts with existing WebFlux setup. Instead, implement custom `WebFilter` for RBAC.\n\n2. **Extend SSE instead of WebSocket** — SSE infrastructure already exists (`subscribeToFlowEvents` in apiClient.ts). Adding WebSocket requires new dependencies and infrastructure. SSE is sufficient for unidirectional server-to-client role updates.\n\n3. **Role Caching with Caffeine** — Backend uses Caffeine cache (already in classpath). Cache profile roles with 5-minute TTL to meet P95 ≤ 10ms latency requirement.\n\n4. **Audit Log as Separate Table** — Follow existing pattern (note_entry table) with PostgreSQL JSONB for flexible metadata.\n\n5. **Header-Based Identity** — Use `X-Profile-Key` (format: `namespace:reference`) and `X-Profile-Auth` headers for identity extraction.\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n\n- All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs must return 403 for unauthorized requests\n- Audit log must capture: timestamp, actor profile key, action (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED), target resource, result\n- Frontend role guards must update within 5 seconds of backend role change\n- RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms\n- Zero breaking changes to existing API contracts\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:RISKS\n\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| RBAC filter performance | High | Caffeine cache with 5min TTL; async audit logging |\n| Cache stale roles | Medium | Cache invalidation on role change via SSE broadcast |\n| SSE connection drops | Low | Auto-reconnect with exponential backoff in frontend |\n| Missing audit logs | Medium | Async logging with error queue; never block request |\n| Profile service unavailable | High | Circuit breaker pattern; fail-closed (deny access) |\n\n---\n\n## Milestones & Iterations\n\n### Phase 1: Backend Foundation (Days 1-3)\n**Goal:** Core RBAC filter and audit infrastructure\n\n#### 1.1 Database Migration\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n# Create audit_log table\n- changeSet:\n    id: rbac-0001-audit-log\n    author: ai-advent\n    context: rbac\n    changes:\n      - createTable:\n          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n          columns:\n            - column:\n                name: id\n                type: UUID\n                defaultValueComputed: gen_random_uuid()\n                constraints:\n                  primaryKey: true\n            - column:\n                name: timestamp\n                type: TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE\n                defaultValueComputed: now()\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: actor_namespace\n                type: VARCHAR(32)\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: actor_reference\n                type: VARCHAR(128)\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: action\n                type: VARCHAR(32)\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: target_resource\n                type: VARCHAR(256)\n            - column:\n                name: target_profile_namespace\n                type: VARCHAR(32)\n            - column:\n                name: target_profile_reference\n                type: VARCHAR(128)\n            - column:\n                name: result\n                type: VARCHAR(16)\n                constraints:\n                  nullable: false\n            - column:\n                name: http_method\n                type: VARCHAR(8)\n            - column:\n                name: http_path\n                type: VARCHAR(512)\n            - column:\n                name: metadata\n                type: JSONB\n      - createIndex:\n          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n          indexName: idx_rbac_audit_timestamp\n          columns:\n            - column:\n                name: timestamp\n      - createIndex:\n          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n          indexName: idx_rbac_audit_actor\n          columns:\n            - column:\n                name: actor_namespace\n            - column:\n                name: actor_reference\n```\n\n#### 1.2 RBAC Core Domain\n**Files to create:**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java` | Enum: ADMIN, USER, VIEWER, etc. |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java` | Value object: namespace + reference |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java` | Enum: READ, WRITE, DELETE, ADMIN |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java` | Record: allowed (boolean), reason (string) |\n\n#### 1.3 RBAC Filter (WebFlux)\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilter.java`\n\n```java\n@Component\n@Order(Ordered.HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE + 100) // After logging, before business logic\npublic class RbacWebFilter implements WebFilter {\n\n    private final ProfileRoleService roleService;\n    private final AuditLogService auditService;\n    private final RbacPathMatcher pathMatcher;\n\n    @Override\n    public Mono<Void> filter(ServerWebExchange exchange, WebFilterChain chain) {\n        HttpMethod method = exchange.getRequest().getMethod();\n        String path = exchange.getRequest().getPath().value();\n\n        // Skip non-mutation methods\n        if (!isMutationMethod(method)) {\n            return chain.filter(exchange);\n        }\n\n        // Skip excluded paths (health, public APIs)\n        if (pathMatcher.isPublicPath(path)) {\n            return chain.filter(exchange);\n        }\n\n        // Extract identity from headers\n        ProfileIdentity identity = extractIdentity(exchange.getRequest());\n        if (identity == null) {\n            return auditAndDeny(exchange, null, path, method, \"Missing identity headers\");\n        }\n\n        // Check required roles for path\n        Set<Role> requiredRoles = pathMatcher.getRequiredRoles(path, method);\n\n        return roleService.hasAnyRole(identity, requiredRoles)\n            .flatMap(hasRole -> {\n                if (hasRole) {\n                    auditService.logAccess(identity, path, method, \"ALLOWED\");\n                    return chain.filter(exchange);\n                } else {\n                    return auditAndDeny(exchange, identity, path, method, \"Insufficient permissions\");\n                }\n            })\n            .onErrorResume(e -> {\n                log.error(\"RBAC check failed\", e);\n                return auditAndDeny(exchange, identity, path, method, \"RBAC error: \" + e.getMessage());\n            });\n    }\n\n    private Mono<Void> auditAndDeny(ServerWebExchange exchange, ProfileIdentity identity,\n                                     String path, HttpMethod method, String reason) {\n        auditService.logDenied(identity, path, method, reason);\n        exchange.getResponse().setStatusCode(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN);\n        exchange.getResponse().getHeaders().setContentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON);\n        String body = String.format(\"{\\\"error\\\":\\\"Forbidden\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"%s\\\"}\", reason);\n        DataBuffer buffer = exchange.getResponse().bufferFactory().wrap(body.getBytes());\n        return exchange.getResponse().writeWith(Mono.just(buffer));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 1.4 Profile Role Service with Caching\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java`\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class ProfileRoleService {\n\n    private final LoadingCache<ProfileIdentity, Set<Role>> roleCache;\n    private final ProfileClient profileClient;\n\n    public ProfileRoleService(ProfileClient profileClient,\n                              @Value(\"${rbac.cache.ttl-minutes:5}\") int cacheTtlMinutes) {\n        this.profileClient = profileClient;\n        this.roleCache = Caffeine.newBuilder()\n            .expireAfterWrite(cacheTtlMinutes, TimeUnit.MINUTES)\n            .maximumSize(10_000)\n            .recordStats()\n            .build(this::loadRoles);\n    }\n\n    private Set<Role> loadRoles(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n        return profileClient.fetchRoles(identity);\n    }\n\n    public Mono<Boolean> hasAnyRole(ProfileIdentity identity, Set<Role> requiredRoles) {\n        if (requiredRoles.isEmpty()) {\n            return Mono.just(true);\n        }\n        return Mono.fromCallable(() -> roleCache.get(identity))\n            .subscribeOn(Schedulers.boundedElastic())\n            .map(userRoles -> userRoles.stream().anyMatch(requiredRoles::contains));\n    }\n\n    public void invalidateCache(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n        roleCache.invalidate(identity);\n    }\n\n    public CacheStats getCacheStats() {\n        return roleCache.stats();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 1.5 Audit Log Service\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/AuditLogService.java`\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class AuditLogService {\n\n    private final AuditLogRepository repository;\n    private final ExecutorService asyncExecutor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(4);\n\n    public void logAccess(ProfileIdentity identity, String path, HttpMethod method, String result) {\n        asyncLog(() -> {\n            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n            entry.setActorNamespace(identity.namespace());\n            entry.setActorReference(identity.reference());\n            entry.setAction(\"ACCESS\");\n            entry.setTargetResource(path);\n            entry.setHttpMethod(method.name());\n            entry.setHttpPath(path);\n            entry.setResult(result);\n            repository.save(entry);\n        });\n    }\n\n    public void logDenied(ProfileIdentity identity, String path, HttpMethod method, String reason) {\n        asyncLog(() -> {\n            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n            if (identity != null) {\n                entry.setActorNamespace(identity.namespace());\n                entry.setActorReference(identity.reference());\n            }\n            entry.setAction(\"DENIED\");\n            entry.setTargetResource(path);\n            entry.setHttpMethod(method.name());\n            entry.setHttpPath(path);\n            entry.setResult(\"DENIED\");\n            entry.setMetadata(Map.of(\"reason\", reason));\n            repository.save(entry);\n        });\n    }\n\n    public void logRoleChange(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target,\n                              String action, Set<Role> roles) {\n        asyncLog(() -> {\n            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n            entry.setActorNamespace(actor.namespace());\n            entry.setActorReference(actor.reference());\n            entry.setAction(action); // GRANT or REVOKE\n            entry.setTargetProfileNamespace(target.namespace());\n            entry.setTargetProfileReference(target.reference());\n            entry.setResult(\"SUCCESS\");\n            entry.setMetadata(Map.of(\"roles\", roles));\n            repository.save(entry);\n        });\n    }\n\n    private void asyncLog(Runnable task) {\n        asyncExecutor.submit(() -> {\n            try {\n                task.run();\n            } catch (Exception e) {\n                log.error(\"Failed to write audit log\", e);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 1.6 Audit Log Entity & Repository\n**Files:**\n- `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java`\n- `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java`\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: Profile Service Integration (Days 4-5)\n**Goal:** Connect to existing profile service for role resolution\n\n#### 2.1 Profile Client\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileClient.java`\n\n```java\n@Component\npublic class ProfileClient {\n\n    private final WebClient webClient;\n    private final String profileServiceUrl;\n\n    public ProfileClient(@Value(\"${profile.service.url}\") String profileServiceUrl,\n                         WebClient.Builder webClientBuilder) {\n        this.profileServiceUrl = profileServiceUrl;\n        this.webClient = webClientBuilder.baseUrl(profileServiceUrl).build();\n    }\n\n    public Set<Role> fetchRoles(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n        try {\n            ProfileResponse response = webClient.get()\n                .uri(\"/api/profiles/{namespace}/{reference}\", identity.namespace(), identity.reference())\n                .retrieve()\n                .bodyToMono(ProfileResponse.class)\n                .timeout(Duration.ofSeconds(2))\n                .block();\n\n            return response != null && response.roles() != null\n                ? response.roles().stream().map(Role::valueOf).collect(Collectors.toSet())\n                : Set.of();\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            log.error(\"Failed to fetch roles for {}\", identity, e);\n            // Fail-closed: return empty set (deny access)\n            return Set.of();\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 2.2 Profile Response DTO\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileResponse.java`\n\n```java\npublic record ProfileResponse(\n    String profileId,\n    String namespace,\n    String reference,\n    List<String> roles,\n    Instant updatedAt\n) {}\n```\n\n#### 2.3 RBAC Configuration\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacConfiguration.java`\n\n```java\n@Configuration\n@EnableConfigurationProperties(RbacProperties.class)\npublic class RbacConfiguration {\n\n    @Bean\n    public RbacPathMatcher rbacPathMatcher(RbacProperties properties) {\n        return new RbacPathMatcher(properties);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacProperties.java`\n\n```java\n@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = \"rbac\")\npublic record RbacProperties(\n    List<PathRule> protectedPaths,\n    List<String> publicPaths,\n    int cacheTtlMinutes\n) {\n    public record PathRule(\n        String path,\n        Set<String> methods,\n        Set<String> requiredRoles\n    ) {}\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: Frontend Role Sync (Days 6-8)\n**Goal:** Real-time role synchronization via SSE\n\n#### 3.1 Extend Profile Store with SSE\n**File:** `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n\n```typescript\n// Add to ProfileStoreState\ntype ProfileStoreState = {\n  // ... existing fields\n  roleVersion: number; // Incremented on role change\n  lastRoleSync: string | null;\n  subscribeToRoleChanges: () => () => void;\n};\n\n// Add to store implementation\nexport const useProfileStore = create<ProfileStoreState>()(\n  persist(\n    (set, get) => ({\n      // ... existing initial state\n      roleVersion: 0,\n      lastRoleSync: null,\n\n      subscribeToRoleChanges: () => {\n        const { namespace, reference, channel, devToken } = getActiveProfileSelection();\n        if (!namespace || !reference) return () => {};\n\n        const params = new URLSearchParams();\n        params.set('namespace', namespace);\n        params.set('reference', reference);\n        if (channel) params.set('channel', channel);\n        if (devToken) params.set('token', devToken);\n\n        const eventSource = new EventSource(\n          `${API_BASE_URL}/api/profiles/role-events?${params.toString()}`\n        );\n\n        eventSource.addEventListener('role-change', (event) => {\n          const data = JSON.parse(event.data);\n          set((state) => ({\n            profile: state.profile ? {\n              ...state.profile,\n              roles: data.roles,\n              updatedAt: data.timestamp,\n            } : null,\n            roleVersion: state.roleVersion + 1,\n            lastRoleSync: new Date().toISOString(),\n          }));\n        });\n\n        eventSource.onerror = () => {\n          // Auto-reconnect handled by browser, but we log it\n          console.warn('Role events connection error, will retry...');\n        };\n\n        return () => eventSource.close();\n      },\n    }),\n    // ... existing persist config\n  ),\n);\n```\n\n#### 3.2 Create useRoleGuard Hook\n**File:** `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n\n```typescript\nimport { useEffect, useMemo } from 'react';\nimport { useProfileStore } from './profileStore';\n\nexport function useRoleGuard(requiredRole?: string) {\n  const roles = useProfileStore((state) => state.profile?.roles ?? []);\n  const roleVersion = useProfileStore((state) => state.roleVersion);\n\n  // Subscribe to role changes on mount\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const unsubscribe = useProfileStore.getState().subscribeToRoleChanges();\n    return unsubscribe;\n  }, []);\n\n  const hasRole = useMemo(() => {\n    if (!requiredRole) return true;\n    return roles.some((role) => role === requiredRole);\n  }, [roles, requiredRole, roleVersion]);\n\n  const hasAnyRole = useMemo(() => {\n    return (roleCodes: string[]) => roles.some((role) => roleCodes.includes(role));\n  }, [roles, roleVersion]);\n\n  const hasAllRoles = useMemo(() => {\n    return (roleCodes: string[]) => roleCodes.every((role) => roles.includes(role));\n  }, [roles, roleVersion]);\n\n  return {\n    roles,\n    hasRole,\n    hasAnyRole,\n    hasAllRoles,\n    isAdmin: roles.includes('admin'),\n    roleVersion,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.3 Update AdminRoles Page\n**File:** `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n\nReplace inline role check with hook:\n\n```typescript\n// Replace lines 34-36:\nconst { isAdmin } = useRoleGuard('admin');\n\n// Replace hasAdminRole references with isAdmin\n```\n\n#### 3.4 Create RoleGuard Component\n**File:** `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n\n```typescript\nimport React from 'react';\nimport { useRoleGuard } from '../lib/useRoleGuard';\n\ninterface RoleGuardProps {\n  requiredRole: string;\n  fallback?: React.ReactNode;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport const RoleGuard: React.FC<RoleGuardProps> = ({\n  requiredRole,\n  fallback = null,\n  children,\n}) => {\n  const { hasRole } = useRoleGuard(requiredRole);\n  return hasRole ? <>{children}</> : <>{fallback}</>;\n};\n\ninterface AdminGuardProps {\n  fallback?: React.ReactNode;\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport const AdminGuard: React.FC<AdminGuardProps> = ({ fallback, children }) => (\n  <RoleGuard requiredRole=\"admin\" fallback={fallback}>\n    {children}\n  </RoleGuard>\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 4: SSE Role Events Endpoint (Days 9-10)\n**Goal:** Backend SSE endpoint for role change notifications\n\n#### 4.1 Role Event Service\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java`\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class RoleEventService {\n\n    private final Map<ProfileIdentity, Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent>> subscribers = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();\n\n    public Flux<RoleChangeEvent> subscribe(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = Sinks.many().multicast().onBackpressureBuffer();\n        subscribers.put(identity, sink);\n\n        return sink.asFlux()\n            .doOnCancel(() -> subscribers.remove(identity))\n            .doOnTerminate(() -> subscribers.remove(identity));\n    }\n\n    public void notifyRoleChange(ProfileIdentity identity, List<String> roles) {\n        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = subscribers.get(identity);\n        if (sink != null) {\n            sink.tryEmitNext(new RoleChangeEvent(roles, Instant.now()));\n        }\n    }\n\n    public void broadcastRoleChange(ProfileIdentity target, List<String> roles) {\n        notifyRoleChange(target, roles);\n    }\n\n    public record RoleChangeEvent(List<String> roles, Instant timestamp) {}\n}\n```\n\n#### 4.2 SSE Controller\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java`\n\n```java\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/profiles\")\npublic class RoleEventsController {\n\n    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n\n    @GetMapping(value = \"/role-events\", produces = MediaType.TEXT_EVENT_STREAM_VALUE)\n    public Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> roleEvents(\n            @RequestParam String namespace,\n            @RequestParam String reference,\n            @RequestParam(required = false) String channel,\n            @RequestParam(required = false) String token) {\n\n        ProfileIdentity identity = new ProfileIdentity(namespace, reference);\n\n        return eventService.subscribe(identity)\n            .map(event -> ServerSentEvent.builder(event)\n                .event(\"role-change\")\n                .id(UUID.randomUUID().toString())\n                .build())\n            .mergeWith(heartbeatFlux());\n    }\n\n    private Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> heartbeatFlux() {\n        return Flux.interval(Duration.ofSeconds(30))\n            .map(i -> ServerSentEvent.<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>builder()\n                .comment(\"heartbeat\")\n                .build());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 4.3 Integrate with Admin Role Operations\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java`\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class RoleAssignmentService {\n\n    private final ProfileClient profileClient;\n    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n    private final AuditLogService auditService;\n    private final ProfileRoleService roleService;\n\n    public Mono<Void> assignRole(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target, Role role) {\n        return profileClient.assignRole(target, role)\n            .doOnSuccess(v -> {\n                // Invalidate cache\n                roleService.invalidateCache(target);\n                // Notify user\n                profileClient.fetchRoles(target)\n                    .thenAccept(roles -> eventService.broadcastRoleChange(target, new ArrayList<>(roles)));\n                // Audit\n                auditService.logRoleChange(actor, target, \"GRANT\", Set.of(role));\n            });\n    }\n\n    public Mono<Void> revokeRole(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target, Role role) {\n        return profileClient.revokeRole(target, role)\n            .doOnSuccess(v -> {\n                roleService.invalidateCache(target);\n                profileClient.fetchRoles(target)\n                    .thenAccept(roles -> eventService.broadcastRoleChange(target, new ArrayList<>(roles)));\n                auditService.logRoleChange(actor, target, \"REVOKE\", Set.of(role));\n            });\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5: Testing & Validation (Days 11-12)\n**Goal:** Comprehensive test coverage\n\n#### 5.1 Backend Tests\n\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilterTest.java`\n\n```java\n@WebFluxTest(RbacWebFilter.class)\nclass RbacWebFilterTest {\n\n    @MockBean\n    private ProfileRoleService roleService;\n\n    @MockBean\n    private AuditLogService auditService;\n\n    @Autowired\n    private WebTestClient webClient;\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldAllowGetRequestWithoutRole() {\n        webClient.get().uri(\"/api/test\")\n            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:test\")\n            .exchange()\n            .expectStatus().isOk();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldDenyPostWithoutRole() {\n        when(roleService.hasAnyRole(any(), any())).thenReturn(Mono.just(false));\n\n        webClient.post().uri(\"/api/test\")\n            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:test\")\n            .exchange()\n            .expectStatus().isForbidden();\n\n        verify(auditService).logDenied(any(), eq(\"/api/test\"), eq(HttpMethod.POST), any());\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldAllowPostWithAdminRole() {\n        when(roleService.hasAnyRole(any(), any())).thenReturn(Mono.just(true));\n\n        webClient.post().uri(\"/api/test\")\n            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:admin\")\n            .exchange()\n            .expectStatus().isOk();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleServiceTest.java`\n\n```java\nclass ProfileRoleServiceTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldCacheRoles() {\n        // First call hits profile service\n        // Second call uses cache\n        // Verify cache stats\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void shouldFailClosedOnError() {\n        // When profile service unavailable\n        // Return empty roles (deny access)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 5.2 Frontend Tests\n\n**File:** `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.test.ts` (new)\n\n```typescript\nimport { renderHook, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport { useRoleGuard } from './useRoleGuard';\nimport { useProfileStore } from './profileStore';\n\ndescribe('useRoleGuard', () => {\n  it('should update when roles change', async () => {\n    const { result } = renderHook(() => useRoleGuard('admin'));\n\n    expect(result.current.hasRole).toBe(false);\n\n    // Simulate role change event\n    useProfileStore.setState({\n      profile: { roles: ['admin'] } as UserProfileDocument,\n      roleVersion: 1,\n    });\n\n    await waitFor(() => {\n      expect(result.current.hasRole).toBe(true);\n    });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n#### 5.3 Integration Tests\n\n**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/RbacIntegrationTest.java`\n\n```java\n@SpringBootTest(webEnvironment = SpringBootTest.WebEnvironment.RANDOM_PORT)\nclass RbacIntegrationTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void endToEndRoleChangeFlow() {\n        // 1. User with viewer role tries POST -> 403\n        // 2. Admin assigns write role\n        // 3. User receives SSE notification\n        // 4. User retries POST -> 200\n        // 5. Audit log contains both DENIED and ALLOWED entries\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 5.4 Performance Tests\n\n```java\n@Test\nvoid rbacLatencyP95Under10ms() {\n    // Run 1000 requests\n    // Measure RBAC check time\n    // Assert P95 < 10ms\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n\n### New Files (Backend)\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java` | Role enum |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java` | Identity VO |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java` | Permission enum |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java` | Decision record |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilter.java` | Main RBAC filter |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java` | Role resolution with cache |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/AuditLogService.java` | Audit logging |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java` | SSE event management |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java` | Role assignment ops |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileClient.java` | Profile service client |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileResponse.java` | Profile DTO |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java` | Audit entity |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java` | Audit repository |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacConfiguration.java` | Config class |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacProperties.java` | Properties record |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/matcher/RbacPathMatcher.java` | Path matching |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java` | SSE endpoint |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml` | Audit table migration |\n\n### Modified Files (Backend)\n\n| Path | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| `backend-mcp/build.gradle` | Add Caffeine cache (if not present) |\n| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java` | Add rbac package to scan |\n\n### New Files (Frontend)\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` | Role guard hook with SSE |\n| `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` | Role guard component |\n| `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.test.ts` | Hook tests |\n\n### Modified Files (Frontend)\n\n| Path | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` | Add SSE subscription, roleVersion |\n| `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` | Use useRoleGuard hook |\n| `frontend/src/App.tsx` | Add RoleGuard for admin nav |\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### application-rbac.yaml\n\n```yaml\nrbac:\n  cache:\n    ttl-minutes: 5\n  protected-paths:\n    - path: \"/api/notes/**\"\n      methods: [\"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\"]\n      required-roles: [\"user\", \"admin\"]\n    - path: \"/api/admin/**\"\n      methods: [\"*\"]\n      required-roles: [\"admin\"]\n  public-paths:\n    - \"/actuator/health\"\n    - \"/api/public/**\"\n    - \"/api/profiles/role-events\"\n\nprofile:\n  service:\n    url: ${PROFILE_SERVICE_URL:http://localhost:8081}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Rollout Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Deploy Backend (Day 13)\n1. Run database migration\n2. Deploy RBAC filter in \"audit-only\" mode (log but don't block)\n3. Monitor audit logs for 24 hours\n\n### Phase 2: Enable Enforcement (Day 14)\n1. Switch RBAC filter to enforcement mode\n2. Monitor 403 rates and latency\n3. Verify cache hit rates\n\n### Phase 3: Frontend Deploy (Day 15)\n1. Deploy updated frontend with SSE subscription\n2. Monitor WebSocket connection rates\n3. Verify role sync within 5 seconds\n\n### Rollback Plan\n- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false)\n- Quick disable via config change\n- Audit logs preserved for analysis\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:ACCEPTANCE\n\n- [ ] AC-1: All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs return 403 for users without required roles\n- [ ] AC-2: All role operations (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED) logged to rbac_audit_log\n- [ ] AC-3: Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of backend change\n- [ ] AC-4: RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms under 1000 RPS load\n- [ ] AC-5: Zero breaking changes to existing public APIs\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:METRICS\n\n| Metric | Target | Measurement |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| RBAC latency P95 | ≤ 10ms | Micrometer timer on filter |\n| Cache hit rate | ≥ 90% | Caffeine cache stats |\n| Role sync delay | ≤ 5s | Frontend timestamp diff |\n| Audit log coverage | 100% | Count vs request volume |\n| 403 error rate | < 1% | HTTP status metrics |\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\n\nNone — all questions resolved via research findings.\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:READ_LOG\n\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileTypes.ts`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts` (excerpt)\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/persistence/NoteEntity.java`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/notes/db.changelog-master.yaml`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/build.gradle`\n\n---\n\n## AIDD:ACTIONS_LOG\n\n- Created plan document with 5 phases\n- Defined 19 new backend files\n- Defined 3 new frontend files\n- Specified 4 modified files\n- Created database migration schema\n- Documented SSE extension approach (vs WebSocket)\n- Documented custom WebFlux filter approach (vs Spring Security)\n\n---\n\n**Status:** READY for implementation\n**Next Action:** Create tasklist and assign to implementer subagent\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":48,"oldLines":14,"newStart":48,"newLines":27,"lines":[" "," ## AIDD:RISKS"," ","-| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |","-|------|--------|------------|","-| RBAC filter performance | High | Caffeine cache with 5min TTL; async audit logging |","-| Cache stale roles | Medium | Cache invalidation on role change via SSE broadcast |","-| SSE connection drops | Low | Auto-reconnect with exponential backoff in frontend |","-| Missing audit logs | Medium | Async logging with error queue; never block request |","-| Profile service unavailable | High | Circuit breaker pattern; fail-closed (deny access) |","+| Risk ID | Description | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |","+|---------|-------------|-------------|--------|------------|","+| R-001 | Profile service unavailable | Medium | High | Circuit breaker; fail-closed; cache roles |","+| R-002 | Cache stale roles after assignment | Medium | Medium | Cache invalidation on role change; TTL 5min |","+| R-003 | SSE connection memory leak | Low | Medium | Proper cleanup on disconnect; subscriber limits |","+| R-004 | Audit log write failures | Low | Medium | Async logging; error queue; never block request |","+| R-005 | RBAC filter performance degradation | Low | High | Caffeine cache; async audit; P95 target 10ms |","+| R-006 | Breaking change to existing APIs | Low | High | Feature flags; audit-only mode first; rollback |","+| R-007 | Component scan misses RBAC beans | Medium | High | Add to all profile configs; verify on startup |","+| R-008 | Missing profile service integration | High | High | Define contract; implement fallback to local DB |"," ","+### Validation-Derived Risks (from TST-001-validation.md)","+","+**R-007: Component Scan Configuration**","+The application uses profile-based component scanning. The RBAC module needs to be added to ALL profiles or a shared configuration created.","+- **Mitigation**: Create `RbacConfig.java` with `@Profile(\"!test\")` active in all non-test profiles","+","+**R-008: Profile Service Integration**","+The plan assumes `profileClient.fetchRoles()` exists, but no backend API for fetching profile roles was found in research.","+- **Mitigation**: Define profile service contract or implement local role storage via `rbac_profile_roles` table","+"," ---"," "," ## Milestones & Iterations"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
